===Etymology===
Traditionally thought to be the same word as {{m+|och|象||elephant}} ([[w:Han Feizi|Han Feizi]][https://ctext.org/hanfeizi/jie-lao#n2005], {{zh-ref|Karlgren, 1957}}).

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} posits that Old Chinese *''z-'' and *''s-l-'' / *''s-j-'' might have merged in {{w|Zuo Zhuan}} and thinks {{m+|och|像||image}} possibly derives from {{der|zh|sit}} root *''la'', making it cognate with {{cog|bo|ལད་མོ||imitation, to imitate, mimic}} & {{m|bo|ལྷ||gods, image of a deity}} (however, see {{m|bo|ལྷ}} for other etymology), {{cog|lep|ᰗᰰ|tr=klan|t=similar}} & {{m|lep|ᰗᰰᰜᰶ|tr=klan-lă|t=imitation}}, {{cog|kac|tr=sum³¹-la³³|t=picture, image}} & {{m|kac|tr=num³¹-la³³|t=ghost}}. {{zh-ref|Geilich (1994)}} adds {{cog|bo|ལྡེམ||statue, idol}} yet connects the {{w|Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman}} items to {{m+|och|似}}.

{{doublet|zh|佯|t1=to feign|樣|t2=appearance}}.

